---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About — astro-build-demo">
  <article class="prose max-w-none py-8">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      This repo holds an Astro project. The source lives in
      <code>astro-build-demo/src</code>, the compiled site lives in
      <code>pages/astro-build-demo</code>, and both are committed so the
      pre-build and post-build content live side by side.
    </p>
    <p>
      To change something, edit any file under
      <code>astro-build-demo/src</code> via the GitHub web UI, then ask
      Claude Code to pull the repo and rebuild. It runs
      <code>npm run build</code> in its sandbox and commits the updated
      <code>pages/astro-build-demo</code>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Never edit <code>pages/astro-build-demo</code> by hand. It is
      generated output, and the next build will quietly overwrite your
      changes.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
